As the U.S. pursues the so-called Indo-Pacific strategy, Japan is acting as its pawn in Asia. But when the U.S. is not strong enough to hold down the "arrow" of Japan, it is bound to suffer severe backlash. Editor: Yuan Xin Chief editor: Ge Jing Managing director: Mei Yan (To submit cartoons and share story ideas or feedback on our cartoon page, please contact us at cartoon_opinions@cgtn.com)